  "text": "PMNs-LECs adhesion assay. The experimental method was modified from that of Yasuda et al [CITATION_1] . LECs were grown until confluent. Before the addition of PMNs, LECs were preincubated with or without anti-P-selectin (10 mg/mL) monoclonal antibody for 30 min. PMNs isolated from blood sample (n = 4) during the mid-luteal phase (1610 6 cell/mL) were added to the cultures in the presence or absence of PGF 2a (10 26 M) for 30 min in DMEM/F-12 medium containing 5% FBS, NaHCO3, gentamicin solution, and amphotericin B solution. After incubation, non-attached cells were washed out 3 times with PBS containing 2% FBS, and 100 mL of citrate buffer (SIGMA) containing 0.1% Triton X-100 was added to each well. After 10 min, 200 mL of o-phenylenediamine dihydrochloride (SIGMA)-citrate buffer solution containing 0.04% H 2 O 2 was added to each well. After incubation at room temperature for 30 min, 50 mL of 4N-H 2 SO 4 was added to stop the reaction, and the myeloperoxidase activity of neutrophils was measured at OD 490 . At least 4 experiments were performed, with each concentration of agents tested with 2 replications/experiments.",
